\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Chapter 4 and 5 analysed complementary aspects of fire weather in Victoria,
 Australia.
 Chapter 4 examined the differences between bushfire and heatwave weather
 patterns.
 On the other hand, Chapter 5 analysed fire weather variability and seasonal
 forecasting skill.
 This chapter aims to test if the findings of these two chapters are robust.
 Chapter 6 reproduces these results using the same methods with alternative
 data sources.
 The chapter consolidates the discussion about fire weather in Victoria
 with consistent results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Four sections comprise this chapter.
 The data and methodology section provides details about the alternative
 data sources.
 It also summarises the methods described in the analogous sections of the
 preceding chapters.
 However, the reader has references to the corresponding chapters for more
 methodological aspects.
 The results section reproduces the findings of chapters 4 and 5.
 The discussion section provides a deeper analysis of the original and reproduce
d results.
 The summary gives an overview of the chapter and highlights the key findings.
